-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group Bank, Komercni Banka, Unipetrol Move
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-04-17T14:56:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/czech-stocks-erste-komercni-banka-kit-digital-unipetrol-move.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
snapped a two-day decline, rising 0.2 percent to 920.80 at its
end of trading in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   of  Austria  rose 1.8 percent
to 391 koruna. Lenders led European shares higher as Spanish
bonds gained and German investor confidence unexpectedly rose.  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)   fell to 3,410 koruna from 3,561
koruna at yesterday’s close as the unit of Societe Generale SA
started trading without the right to a 160 koruna dividend.
Adjusted for the payout, the stock increased 0.3 percent.  Unipetrol AS (UNIP)  , the biggest Czech oil refiner, slid
1.2 percent to 171 koruna. Industry and Trade Minister Martin Kuba proposed a new tax on motor fuels, E15 newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
